sentences: Aaron Jeoffrey Benward (born September 13, 1973) is an American singer-songwriter, actor, film/tv producer and music supervisor.
In high school, he left his mark as an All-State football, basketball and soccer player and was named the U.S. Army Scholar/Athlete of the Year.
In 1991, he surprised his father Jeoffrey when he told his dad that he wanted to follow his steps in the music business.
Aaron met his wife, Kenda, in San Jose, California, and married in 1994.
In the late 1990s, Aaron decided to pursue a solo career.
After recovering from his injuries, Mr. Benward was able to release his debut album titled Imagine, that had Billboard #1 single called "Captured" in 2000.

In 2009, Aaron, co-created a live show in Las Vegas called "Nashville Unplugged: The Story Behind the Song", that features hit songwriters from all genres in a back porch, songwriter in the round style show made famous at the Bluebird Cafe in Nashville, Tn.
"Nashville Unplugged" is 11 years running and currently plays every Friday night at 8 PM in Las Vegas at Mandalay Bay Hotel and Casino.

In March 2012 til March 2014,  Aaron moved his creative forces and his family to Los Angeles and signed a new exclusive music publishing deal with Cornman Music/Warner Chappell where he had numerous songs placed on shows like ABC's "Nashville" and Bravo's "Project Runway".

In March 2012 til March 2014,  Aaron moved his creative forces and his family to Los Angeles and signed a new exclusive music publishing deal with Cornman Music/Warner Chappell where he had numerous songs placed on shows like ABC's "Nashville" and Bravo's "Project Runway".
In May 2015, Aaron co-wrote and co-produced the theme song and end title for Walt Disney's "Monkey Kingdom" called "It's our World" performed by Atlantic Records artist Jacquie Lee.

Since December 2015, Aaron has co-written 15 songs that have been recorded by some of the biggest recording artists in JPOP and KPOP music such as EXO, Namie Amuro, AOA, Taeyeon, Taemin and Red Velvet with 9 of those songs becoming big hits in SE ASIA.
Currently, Aaron has had 20 songs in the hit Netflix series "The Ranch" starring Ashton Kutcher, Sam Elliott and Debra Winger.
Recently, Aaron has taken his talents to the silver screen by starring in 3 films called "Acts of God", "The Song" and "Past Due".
"The Song" was picked up by Metro-Goldwyn and released in September 2014.

Aaron is a partner in Watershed Motion Pictures and has recently released their first feature film called “Playing God” starring Luke Benward, Michael McKean, Alan Tudyk, Marc Menchaca and Jude Demorest.
Watershed is currently in production on their latest feature called Chasing Oslo.
He finished principal photography on “Quiet in My Town” on October 24, 2019 in Thomasville, Ga, which is an independent feature film that pulls back the secrets of a small town.
It's due to be released in 2021.

Aaron and Watershed have recently partnered with Jared Goetz of Ascending Media Group and John Bryan of JB and Associates to represent their latest project called God Family Football which is a new Docu-series that follows the Evangel Christian Academy football program in Shreveport, LA and their football coach and pastor, Denny Duron.
